Media Relations

03.09.2013
Bank J. Safra Sarasin strengthens Asset Management Team
Bank J. Safra Sarasin today announced the appointment of four highly experienced professionals to its Asset Management team.  
Florian Esterer is the new Head Asset Management Equities and will be joined by Thomas Zbinden, Senior Portfolio Manager and Christoph Lang, Portfolio Manager. 
In addition Helmut Kotschwar is appointed to the new role of Head Investment Centre and will be responsible for portfolio construction across all asset management units. 
These appointments bring a significant track record from their previous roles at Swisscanto, SAM Sustainable Asset Management, Credit Suisse and Zurich Kantonalbank. The gentlemen have extensive expertise in equity strategies, portfolio management, sustainable investment and client relations across all major global markets.
Dr. Jan A. Poser, Head Asset Management of Bank J. Safra Sarasin, said:"We are delighted to strengthen our Asset Management team with these significant new appointments. They have a proven track record in international portfolio management and reinforce the Bank's global leadership in sustainable investment. We continue to attract high caliber professionals enabling us to deliver a rigorous and prudent investment process which is highly valued by our clients."
        
Florian Esterer – Head Asset Management Equities
A German and Swiss citizen (42), Mr Esterer has joined from MainFirst where since 2011 he was a Senior Portfolio Manager for global equities.
From 2003 to 2011 he worked for Swisscanto and headed the global equities team with CHF2.5bn assets under management. Before joining Swisscanto, he was – among other assignments – a consultant with the Boston Consulting Group.
Florian Esterer is a CFA charter holder, president of the CFA Society Switzerland and holds an MBA from the American University, Washington DC.

Helmut Kotschwar - Head Investment Centre
A German citizen (51), Mr Kotschwar has joined from SAM Sustainable Asset Management where since 2008 he was Senior Investment Strategist and Head Portfolio Analysis. From 1993-2007 he held senior portfolio roles with Siemens in the financial services division. He started his career in private banking with Hauckbankiers in Frankfurt.
Helmut Kotschwar is a CFA charter holder and holds a master’s degree in economics from the HWV of Kassel, Germany.

Thomas Zbinden – Senior Portfolio Manager
A Swiss citizen (48), Mr Zbinden has joined from Swisscanto where since 2007 he was Senior Portfolio Manager. From 1994-2007 he held senior equity portfolio roles with Credit Suisse Asset Management and Private Banking. He started his career with Bank von Ernst & Cie in Berne.
Thomas Zbinden is an EFFAS certified analyst and holds a degree in economics from the University of Berne.

Christoph Lang – Portfolio Manager
A German citizen (29), Mr Lang has joined from Zurich Kantonal Bank where since 2010 he was Senior Quant Portfolio Manager. He conducted his traineeship with ZKB and with Standard Chartered Bank.
Christoph Lang is a CFA charter holder and holds a degree in economics and business administration from the University of Hohenheim, Germany.
    
Media release with pictures
      



